  "records": {
    "description": "A Sequential Shulker Unloader optimized to be small and cheap by using more redstone dust than observers. It is inspired by previous designs by HeilzMaker and SamosTheSage.",
    "features": [
      "Optimized to be small and cheap",
      "Each slice filters items at max 1x hopper speed",
      "The box loader is fully reliable",
      "Includes an end slice with unloader, mixed loader, and empty box recycling"
    ],
    "considerations": [
      "Dust may be less lag-friendly than observers, but none of the dust is constantly clocked here, it only activates per box, so there wasn't a noticeable difference in my testing."
    ],
    "instructions": [
      "Expand or trim the tiled version to desired number of slices",
      "Set the item filters at ss15 with 4 unstackable blockers like: [63 B B B B] or [15 B B B B]",
      "Make sure you have enough storage space for output boxes (full, mixed, and empty)",
      "Input mixed boxes and wait for them to process"
    ]
  },
